<Author>Don_Cuevas
<Content>Hotel Stanza: a decent place to stay in Col. Roma Nte. We usually like to stay in the Centro Hist贸rico, but on our return from the U.S wanted to be in Colonia Roma, so we could experience a new area as well as walk to friends' house.The Hotel Stanza was more than adequate; the lobby was smoky but tolerable; the room we had was very spacious, airconditioned and had a large bathroom. There were two minir flaws: the wi-fi connections were constantly interrupted, and when I put my laptop in a cabinet, the door fell off!Rather than eat at the attached Wings Restaurante, we opted for the flagship Bisquets Obreg贸n, which while nothing special, served decent food at affordable prices.The staff was helpful and largely bilingual.It's a good option if you wish to stay in Colonia Roma Norte. (By the way, we didn't notice any bad smell as mentioned by a previous reviewer. That may have been a temporary problem.) 
